<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-17T13:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-17T13:54:00-05:00" n="721" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d721">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">785.00/10–3151: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United
                                    Kingdom</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d721fn1">This telegram, drafted by U. Alexis
                                Johnson, summarized the substance of a conversation which he had
                                held with Mr. Tomlinson of the British Embassy on the preceding
                                day.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-17T13:54:00-05:00">November
                                    17, 1951—1:54 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2564. Re <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 2118 Oct 31. Dept has
                            informed Brit Emb rep here <pb facs="1163" n="1147" xml:id="pg_1147"/>
                            that our intelligence auths entirely agree with estimate Brit mil intel
                            concerning potential use Yalu dam as communications line and that in
                            discussions with Morrison this subject Sec had not been correctly
                            briefed. However, we pointed out as also stated by Sec to Morrison, dam
                            is very important source electric power for Port Arthur, Dairen
                            industrial and military complex.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>